# commit message format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
# 
# type can be:
#   feat:     new feature
#   fix:      bug fix
#   docs:     documentation update
#   style:    code format (no impact on code running)
#   refactor: refactor (neither new feature nor bug fix)
#   perf:     performance optimization
#   test:     add test
#   chore:    build process or auxiliary tool change
#
# scope is optional, for example:
#   feat(api): add user authentication interface
#   fix(db): fix database connection leak
#
# subject is a short description of the change:
#   - use present tense ("add" instead of "added")
#   - do not capitalize the first letter
#   - do not end with a period 
